org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulator.mutable.common

Class AbstractSingleData<T,M extends DataManipulator<M,I>,I extends ImmutableDataManipulator<I,M>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulator.mutable.common.AbstractData<M,I>
      • org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulator.mutable.common.AbstractSingleData<T,M,I>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of single value this will hold
    M - The type of DataManipulator
    I - The type of ImmutableDataManipulator
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataSerializable, DataManipulator<M,I>, ValueContainer<M>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractBooleanData, AbstractBoundedComparableData, AbstractIntData, AbstractListData, AbstractMappedData, AbstractSingleCatalogData, AbstractSingleEnumData

    public abstract class AbstractSingleData<T,M extends DataManipulator<M,I>,I extends ImmutableDataManipulator<I,M>>
extends AbstractData<M,I>
    An abstraction for the various DataManipulators that handle a single value, adding the provided getValue() and setValue(Object) methods for easy manipulation. This as well simplifies handling various other common implementations, such as hashCode() and equals(Object).
